V2.51 (28.3.2008): (english)

 - fixed strange "hits on exit" issue under
   MorphOS (reproduceable with a random component)

 - when in "Area" mode and either "Crop", "Cut",
   "CutInverse" or "Move" operators are executed,
   the area parameters now are applied on the full
   image (instead of the selection, which would fail
   with an error); afterwards "Area" mode is left due
   to size change; i.e. now these operations do work
   intuitively also when in Area mode...

 - during "Area" selection, the current mouse X/Y
   position or - once dragging a box - the W/H size
   of the selected rectangle now is displayed in the
   window title bar
 - during "Area" selection it is now ensured that
   position/size under/overflows (relative to window
   size) are not possible anymore (previously this
   caused an regular error as well, but later on)

 - fixed a number of gaps and bugs in SView5.cpinfo

 - updated spanish .guide (base: v2.50)
   (-> Damaso Dominguez)

 - saving/loading SView.config from current directory
   is no longer supported (either ENV: or PROGDIR:)

 - included sview5.library V15.12 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.50 (21.3.2008): (english)

 - Tools:

   - WinSlide, ScrollSlide:

      - fixed possible blitter race condition

 - Plugins:

   - ImageFX (Saver):

      - fixed possible blitter race condition

 - updated spanish translations of many files
   including the .guide again (base: v2.49)
   (-> Damaso Dominguez)

 - cleaned up "known bugs" in .guide

 - included sview5.library V15.11 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.49 (15.3.2008): (english)

 - in SlideView mode JPEG EXIF thumbnails now are utilized
 - fixed again metadata flagging in file info dialog
 - updated .readme and .guide file again
 - extended online help function with .guide links to new gadgets

 - included sview5.library V15.10 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.48 (9.3.2008): (english)

 - ARexx: - gfxtype no longer considered part of metadata
          - stripmeta cannot be reverted via GUI anymore
          - added togglemeta (toggles boolean checkmark,
            i.e. flag whether to save metadata)
          - added loadmeta=file command (loads metadata from file)
          - added fixmeta command (same as meta-fix GUI checkbox)

 - added AddMeta button (imports [foreign] metadata from external file);
   this survives also image processing
 - added StripMeta button (works like StripMeta ARexx command)
 - added Meta-Fix button which makes any kind of meta data
   survive also image processing, i.e. modifications of the
   original context of meta data (otherwise lost by default)
 - fixed some minor glitches here and there
 - presence of either XMP0 or XMP1 metadata now indicated in
   file info dialog (before: just EXIF or IPTC)

 - included sview5.library V15.9 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.47 (3.3.2008): (english)

 - ARexx port (name) default config now more robust ("SViewII.rx")
   (-> Dr. Heiko Pollmeier)
 - App port name fixed (now "SView5.app")

V2.46 (24.2.2008): (english)

 - PNG-Box5, JPEG-Box5 and GIF-Box5 now also "remember"
   the path settings of SView5 and can handle spaces
   in filenames
 - undo and exchange buffer naming previously did not allow
   for more than one SView5 instance running in parallel

 - included sview5.library V15.7 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.45 (16.2.2008): (english)

 - included sview5.library V15.6 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.44 (3.2.2008): (english)

 - "getinfo=gfxalpha" Arexx command could have returned wrong value
    due to missing gfxbuffer version check; e.g. after stripalpha
    operation
    (-> Roland Heyder)

 - PNG-Box5, JPEG-Box5 and GIF-Box5 now directly can be started
   from within SView5 by menu or hotkey (menu shortcut);
   the graphics which currently is loaded in SView5 is
   passed on directly to the called tool

 - included sview5.library V15.5 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.43 (27.1.2008): (english)

 - "undo" could have crashed due to RGFX bug
 - fixed V2.41 history

 - included sview5.library V15.4 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.42 (26.1.2008): (english)

 - @{"8/48 >> 24" LINK GADGET_8to24} now became a cycle
   gadget with three options:

    - "--"           (do nothing)
    - "8|48 >> 24"   (convert to 24 bit always)
    - "auto 8|24|48" (convert to anything needed, after error)

   i.e. it will be tried to do some operation and in case the
   required data format does not match the current one, it will
   be retried after conversion into the required format (upto 2x).

   When in "area selection" mode, this gadget is disabled,
   since here we operate in 24 bit automatically.
 - fixed .guide entries on the new options

 - included sview5.library V15.3 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.41 (20.1.2008): (english)

 - fixed Enforcer hits in picture info requester,
   which did not occur under MOS for some reason
   (-> Thomas Klein)
 - picture info requester layout shrunken
 - picture info requester now also indicates presence
   of IPTC or EXIF chunks/sets
 - if the size of an image is or becomes smaller than
   8x8 pixel the graphical area selection and color
   selection is disabled now (hard to hit anything then)
 - fixed SVO destination bit-depth indication;
   no longer indicates 24 bit for <= 8 bit or metadata
 - added UNDO=<ON|OFF> CTA command
   (-> Roland Heyder)
 - new "8 >> 24" gadget now became "8/48 >> 24" gadget,
   also auto-converting 48 bit graphics
   (-> Roland Heyder)
 - added AUTOCONV=<OFF|24> command (to be extended)
   which works similar to the new GUI checkbox
   (-> Roland Heyder)
 - added STRIPMETA ARexx command as one-time action
   which toggles the boolean decision (whether to keep
   the metadata or not) to FALSE

 - added some more sub-commands to GETINFO ARexx command

    - for retrieving EXIF data size (or check if present)
    - for retrieving IPTC data size (or check if present)

 - fixed bug in GETINFO ARexx command

    - all the metadata gfx... commands had a race condition

 - updated ARexx scripts to demo new commands

 - Tools:

   - JPEG-Box5:

      - removed some dead code from 030 version (makefile)

   - PNG-Box5:

      - removed some dead code from 030 version (makefile)

   - GIF-Box5:

      - removed some dead code from 030 version (makefile)
      - fixed also *this* copy of old, broken endianess macro...
      - replaced encoder with latest version
      - supports writing 24 bit tiled GIF files now

 - included sview5.library V15.2 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.40 (12.1.2008): (english)

 - "Undo" now now also triggers auto-display-after-action
   if checked/enabled
 - added new "8 >> 24" gadget which enforces 24 bit
   conversion on loading (useful when doing a number
   of image processing operations in a row and you
   do not want to call AnyTo24Bit each time manually)
   see @{"8 >> 24" LINK GADGET_8to24}
 - added new "META" gadget which allows to decide
   whether metadata (author, ... or EXIF/IPTC data)
   should be kept when 1:1 converting a graphics or not;
   as soon as image processing starts this data is
   lost in any case; it also is lost when the destination
   file format does not support metadata
   see @{"META" LINK GADGET_META}

 - included sview5.library V15.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.39 (6.1.2008): (english)

 - "Undo" now active by default
 - updated SView5.cpinfo (see library)
 - Copyright bump to 2008

 - Plugins:

   - ImageFX:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import (loader)
      - increased library requirements (loader/saver)

   - PPaint:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import (loader)
      - updated version information (outdated)

   - PageStream:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import (loader)
      - increased library requirements (loader/saver)

   - AdPro:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import (loader)
      - increased library requirements (loader/saver)
      - added AdPro.cpinfo (see library)

 - Tools:

   - WinSlide:

      - added option KEYCLOSE that can be combined
        with CLOSEGAD
      - fixed window title texts according to
        actual config (CLOSEGAD, KEYCLOSE, nothing)

   - JPEG-Box5:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import
      - optimized memory allocations
      - fixed HAM detection routine (forgotten copy-paste)
      - increased library requirements
      - Copyright bump to 2008 (and fix)
      - now calls WinSlide with KEYCLOSE, allows
        to close window by keypress

   - PNG-Box5:

      - fixed HAM detection routine (forgotten copy-paste)
      - increased library requirements
      - Copyright bump to 2008 (and fix)
      - upgraded to libpng 1.2.24
      - libpng config for 030 version now same as 000 version
        (tRNS handling)
      - now calls WinSlide with KEYCLOSE, allows
        to close window by keypress

   - GIF-Box5:

      - now finally rejects 48 bit import (like 24 bit)
      - fixed HAM detection routine (forgotten copy-paste)
      - increased library requirements
      - replaced wrong GUI gfx and removed it
      - Copyright bump to 2008 (and fix)
      - now calls WinSlide with KEYCLOSE, allows
        to close window by keypress

 - included sview5.library V14.6 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

