   this means the name is no longer operator_SQ but SQoperator

V2.20 (3.3.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V10.10 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.19 (28.2.2007): (english)

 - due to a missing gfxbuffer version check,
   the gfxbuffer info window could have reported
   "alpha" sometimes, even if the alpha information
   already had been stripped previously (e.g. by
   a 24 bit to 8 bit dithering operation)
 - optimized ARexx, WB Tooltypes and Config option
   parsing (faster)
 - added two new ARexx commands for saving screens,
   with wildcard support, i.e. now you can grab
   screens using a pattern like "ScreenName #?"
 - other minor optimizations

 - included sview5.library V10.9 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.18 (17.2.2007): (english)

 - removed STATUS ARexx command
 - added new "GETINFO=command" Arexx command, which
   allows to retrieve certain information (details
   specified by command); currently program/library
   version and basic GfxBuffer information can be
   retrieved, in the future more options may be added
   (=> @{"details" LINK Control})
 - completely reworked the content of the "ARexx-Scripts"
   folder (including the scripts themselves, the readme,
   and the annoying usage of T: - which is now VMEM:)
 - fixed bug with extra space at end of some file type
   names w/o subtype which would not have been available
   via ARexx due to the extra space (e.g. "DEEP ")
 - fixed older history entries slightly
 - installer script changes:

     - fixed percentages
     - sview5.library now always installed at last
     - no longer copies SViewIV config files in case
       there is no SView5 config file in ENV: or ENVARC:

 - included sview5.library V10.8 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

