      - updated date and copyright information

   - JPEG-Box:

      - increased minimum sview5.library requirements to V10
      - increased minimum sview5support.library requirements to V3
      - updated date and copyright information

 - added two more checkbox gadgets, one for the Save button
   and one for symmetry (yet always disabled)
 - the checkbox button besides the Save button now activates
   the automatic generation of the default file extension
   (e.g. .ilbm/.png/.jpg) when opening the file requester
   prior to saving a file; note that it is still possible
   to just ignore this recommendation and change the file
   name not to have an extension; ARexx is not affected
   by the checkbox setting
 - opening any file requester now causes a busy mouse pointer
 - added new ARexx command "AREASELECT" for selecting an
   SVOperator action area via Arexx (instead of the GUI)
 - added support for new "AREA" .cpinfo data type, which
   allows to select an area visually and pass the
   rectangle coordinates as ControlPad parameter
   to SV#? modules in form "SV_AREA=left,top,width,height";
   e.g. as parameter to Cut/Crop SV5Operator;
   NOTE: this works on a real graphics visually only,
         in case there is one loaded (otherwise manually
         entering a string is required);
         any previously selected "global" area will be
         released, then; selection of a global area
         on the other hand will overwrite (delete)
         a previous local SV_AREA in the .controlpad
 - added support for new "COLOR_#?" .cpinfo data types,
   which allow to select a color/component visually and pass
   the result as ControlPad parameter to SV#? modules
   e.g. as parameter to AddAlpha SV5Operator;
   OR when e.g. selecting the transparent color of a GIF/PNG
   image prior to saving it (cf. GIF-Box5/PNG-Box5)
   NOTE: this works on a real graphics visually only,
         in case there is one loaded (otherwise manually
         entering a string is required)
 - results of SV5Operators which result in de-facto size changes
   will be rejected for area operations now (size mismatch error)
 - SV5Operators which have the -new- "size change" flag set,
   are rejected for area operations (size mismatch error)
 - the 4 CTA commands for ASL file requester dimension settings
   have been replaced by a single new one (you will have to
   redo your settings)
 - after using an ASL file requester the first time, size
   and position are not remembered (and saved into the configuration
   in case it is saved afterwards); no more need to manually hack
   it into your configuration file the first time
 - the default file requester size/pos now is always determined
   from the screen size using a simple formula
 - added new CTA command VISUAL_PREFS for controlling the new
   visual area/color selection mechanism (on/off - default is on)
 - the SV5Driver settings are no longer globally changed for
   all programs, but only locally within SView5 (regardless
   whether changed on the GUI, via Config or via Arexx)
 - increased minimum sview5.library requirements to V10
 - also updated the .guide file regarding sview5(support).library
   minimum requirements
 - etc. etc. etc.
 - included sview5.library V10.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.00 (14.1.2007): (english)

 - fixed a number of icon positions
 - removed obsolete options from SView5.cpinfo
 - added two (four) new buttons for 2 new features;
   one yet remains disabled
 - added unlimited UNDO functionality (uses VMEM:)
 - added two more checkboxes to the GUI which allow
   for automatic display (when enabled) of
   graphics right after "Load" or "Action";
   this saves you from pressing "View" each time
 - slightly re-arranged the existing buttons to
   make the new checkboxes fit at the right places
 - updated spanish guide and GUI catalog (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - added missing protection bits to Quickstart batch files
   (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - now explicitely copy all the Quickstart files including
   icons when creating the LHA (no more pattern matching -
   wonder who wrote that part for MorphOS/FFS)
   (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - extended german/english guide with online help for
   new GUI buttons (also added support in code)
 - minimum requirements increased to sview5.library V9+
   and sview5support.library V3+
 - fixed sv#? library-version related texts in all catalogs;
   fixed some bogus texts in some, while at it
 - included sview5.library V9.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V1.99 (11.1.2007): (english)

 - internal beta release for "pswx-beta" Yahoo testers

V1.95 (6.1.2007): (english)

 - no longer writes .info files in case the destination
   SVObject is of type "Device" (e.g. Printer or FxPaint StarGate)
 - this by the way did overwrite the icon of the original image
 - included sview5.library V8.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes several major fixes & improvements

V1.93 (27.12.2006): (english)

 - included sview5.library V7.4 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes several major fixes & improvements

V1.92 (26.12.2006): (english)

 - fixed a problem with ControlPads and extra chars in paths

 - included sview5.library V7.3 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes several major fixes & improvements

V1.91 (11.12.2006): (english)

 - made sure, that all executables now explicitely
   get the rwed flags set right after compiling

 - included sview5.library V7.2 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes some fixes & improvements

V1.90 (12.11.2006): (english)

 - various fixes in the .guide file

 - included sview5.library V7.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes many fixes & improvements

V1.85 (25.10.2006): (english)

 - updated a number of spanish translations,
   including the catalog files (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - removed some old akmpeg references from the .guide
 - added/fixed a number of icons (yet still old-style)
 - main program version still was 1.84 for 1.85

 - included sview5.library V6.6 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes many fixes & improvements

V1.84 (5.10.2006): (english)

 - PictureInfo:
    - fixed problem with INVALID_ID and HAM/EHB flag recognition
    - a changed screenmode was not updated on the GUI (fixed)

 - included sview5.library V6.5 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes many fixes & improvements

V1.83 (24.9.2006): (english)

 - included sview5.library V6.4 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
   which includes numerous fixes & improvements
 - included updated installer script with
   spanish strings by Damaso Dominguez
 - using PagePrint.sv5operator it's now possible
   to create thumbnail overview pages

V1.82 (10.9.2006): (english)

 - included sview5.library V6.3 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V1.81 (30.8.2006): (english)

 - included sview5.library V6.2 hotfix (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
 - finetuned behaviour in case sview5.library could
   not be opened

V1.80 (28.8.2006): (english)

 - included sview5.library V6.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V1.74 (30.7.2006): (english)

 - Tools:

   - PNG-Box:

      - PNG-Box now can read, modify and write PNG ICON information
      - added separate tab for modification of icon chunk content
      - note: since the icon-chunk reader is more tolerant than the one
              from Ambient (not using libpng for that particular
              part of work) it might be possible to recover non-standard
              compliant icon files this way
      - fixed bugs with multi transparency: now read-only

V1.73 (19.6.2006): (english)

 - Tools:

   - minor fixes to the 4 viewer programs (#?Slide)
   - minor tix to BatchProcess tool

 - SView:

   - fixed some strlen() issues
   - removed some unused keyfile code
   - removed external MPEG support

V1.72 (30.5.2006): (english)

 - ASL multi-selection does not work under the WB of AOS4/MOS which
   caused the filerequester of CyberSlide, SuperSlide, ScrollSlide
   and WinSlide not to deliver any selection results at all;
   added fallback-option in case the multi-selection result
   is zero - in this case the single-selection will be taken;
   CLI usage was not affected

V1.71 (13.4.2006): (english)

 - included updated sview5.library V5.2

V1.70 (26.2.2006): (english)

 - SView5: - 24 Bit and Alpha (32 Bit) support now is
             indicated on the GUI (for SVObject Savers)

           - starting from sview5.library V5
             SView5 uses its own internal info requester,
             which is font-sensitive, provides additional
             information and allows to change the viewmode
             (with older library versions it uses the
              old approach, which is driven by the SVObjects)

 - included updated sview5.library V5.1

V1.67 (4.2.2006): (english)

 - included updated sview5.library with some new operators:

     - AlphaBlend
     - FixAlphaBlend
     - AddAlpha
     - InvertAlpha
     - StripAlpha
     - ExtractAlpha
     - AddTransColor

 - PPaint plugin:

     - no longer saves settings to ENVARC: (only ENV:)
     - fixed some compatibility issues with sview5.library
     - now imports and exports single-color transparency
       for (upto) 8 bit images
     - all the loaders/savers now start with "SV5" instead
       of "SV" and the priority was decreased from 9000
       to 8999 - this should fix problems when the old
       sview io library is installed in parallel

 - AdPro plugin:

     - Loader: now imports alpha channel into AdPro, if present
     - Saver:  unfortunately export is not possible (not documented)

 - Tools:

     - fixed PNG-Box5, JPEG-Box5 and GIF-Box5 copyright & layout
     - fixed TRNS check in PNG-/GIF-Box5
     - PNG-Box now indicates multi-color transparency PNGs
     - PNg-Box now allows to modify PNG filter settings

 - SView5:

     - fixed problem with spaces in pathnames when calling external player
       or executing rexx scripts from menu
     - fixed garbage wildcard in certain file requesters associated
       with .cpinfo preferences settings
     - strip control characters from viewmode name before loading, saving
       or processing it (e.g. under MOS this may occur)

V1.66 (13.1.2006): (english)

 - PPaint plugin was not included
 - bumped date (2005/06)
 - finally fixed problem in the SV-Lib install script as
   reported by Jean Marie Boucher on 29.05.05
 - the .cd files for translations were missing since some time
 - fixed some catalog entries
 - officially turned into "donation ware"

